JOHANNESBURG - IFP founder Emeritus Mangosuthu Buthelezi's family on Wednesday announced that he has been discharged from hospital. The 93-year-old had been admitted to hospital after suffering from hypertension. In a short statement, his family thanked the public for its support. "We are pleased to report that after a brief period of recuperation and resting, he has been given a clean bill of health and was discharged from hospital yesterday [Tuesday]." They also thanked the medical team that treated the prince. "It is good to have him back home at KwaPhindangene where he is preparing for the upcoming opening of Parliament and State of the Nation debate." He had also recently contracted COVID-19. His doctors said it was wise to admit him to hospital to undergo all the necessary checks.